HEADWORD: Concoctive
<hw>Con*coct"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having the power
of digesting or ripening; digestive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hence the <qex>concoctive</qex> powers, with various art,⟦br⟧
Subdue the cruder aliments to chyle.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Armstrong.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concolor</ent>⟦br⟧
